<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-12-31T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-01-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="288" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d288">
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi></head>
                            <p>Since Benghazi had been designated co-capital of Libya in December
                                1953, the Consulate in Benghazi was designated a Legation, along
                                with the Legation in Tripoli, in February 1954.</p>
                        </div>
